Hello,

SSH keys are more secure than passwords, no doubt. Yet managing multiple keys is usually harder than managing multiple passwords. This email will show you how to import, generate, and manage multiple SSH keys. And it will be easy.

🔑 *Keychain* is where you can find your SSH keys, passkeys, identities, and certificates in Termius.

🆕 *Generate a new SSH key in Termius.* Name it for easier management and export it to selected hosts. It will automatically add the new key to the server and allow you to connect more securely.

➕ *Add your existing keys to Termius.* Paste your existing SSH keys from the clipboard or import them from the filesystem. Once added, attach your keys to the hosts and connect.

*🪪 Rotate keys using identity.* Set a username, attach your key, and link it to your hosts and groups. When it's time to rotate, update the key identity, and all hosts are updated.

Tomorrow, we will show you how to use hardware keys: FIDO2, Yubikey, and Biometric keys.

